{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/14843", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/14843/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/14843/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/14843/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/14843", "id": 35567735, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUzNTU2NzczNQ==", "number": 14843, "title": "DynamicLibrary symbols can outlive their handle + crash", "user": {"login": "tomjakubowski", "id": 667901, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjY2NzkwMQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/667901?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski", "html_url": "https://github.com/tomjakubowski", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2014-06-12T10:20:18Z", "updated_at": "2014-06-12T12:27:15Z", "closed_at": "2014-06-12T12:27:15Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "For example this compiles and segfaults:\n\n``` rust\n// baz.rs\n#![crate_id=\"baz\"]\n#![crate_type=\"dylib\"]\n\n#[no_mangle]\npub fn plus5(x: int) -> int {\n    x + 5\n}\n\n// foo.rs\npub fn main() {\n    use std::dynamic_lib::DynamicLibrary;\n    let baz = DynamicLibrary::open(Some(&Path::new(\"libbaz.dylib\")));\n    let baz = baz.unwrap();\n\n    let plus5: fn(int) -> int = unsafe { \n        baz.symbol(\"plus5\").unwrap()\n    };\n    drop(baz); // handle to loaded library is freed, invalidating plus5\n    println!(\"{}\", plus5(4)); // segfaults\n}\n```\n\nI see there's a comment on `DynamicLibrary::symbol` that mentions this lifetime issue. The fix seems easy (return a `Result<&'a T, _>`, adjust user code accordingly), but also like a headache for some downstream users like `rustc::plugin` that [rely on being able to leak DynamicLibrary instances](https://github.com/mozilla/rust/blob/1635ef2a1958749e7b0cf4e812e1a87cd919027f/src/librustc/plugin/load.rs#L138-L141).\n\nIf this behavior is acceptable, it could at least be documented on the method.\n", "closed_by": {"login": "tomjakubowski", "id": 667901, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjY2NzkwMQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/667901?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski", "html_url": "https://github.com/tomjakubowski", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions"